{"id":83712,"title":"[Disease as a phenomenon of human nature: toward understanding and developing of V.Kh.Vasilenko's philosophical legacy. Part 2].","abstract":"Empirical data on the nature of disease were systematized and summarized in Part 1. In Part 2 the same problem is addressed by the deductive method from the general biological and philosophical standpoint. Methodological assessment of the most popular definitions of the disease is undertaken along with expanded medico-philosophical interpretation of the notion of disease as an anthropological phenomenon including its applied aspects.","date":"2014-10-01","categories":"Pathological Conditions and Signs and Symptoms","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25269203","annotations":[{"name":"Philosophy","weight":0.835806,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philosophy"},{"name":"Phenomenon","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Phenomenon"},{"name":"Deductive reasoning","weight":0.756683,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deductive_reasoning"},{"name":"Nature","weight":0.747438,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nature"},{"name":"Anthropology","weight":0.735806,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthropology"},{"name":"Human nature","weight":0.72,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_nature"},{"name":"Empirical","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Empirical"},{"name":"Human","weight":0.649308,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human"},{"name":"Biology","weight":0.637578,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biology"},{"name":"Data","weight":0.553926,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.435138,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Interpretation (logic)","weight":0.115641,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interpretation_(logic)"},{"name":